Four people were arrested for alleged robbery on Saturday near Camperdown, outside Pietermaritzburg. Shaheen Suleiman of Magma Security said a man robbed was of all his belongings and then thrown out of the moving vehicle close to Camperdown. He said a look-out was flagged for a taxi with an NC registration. Suleiman said Magma reaction officers picked up the taxi in Pietermaritzburg and the local police units arrived to assist. The man’s cell phone and bank cards were recovered in the taxi. “The four suspects have been detained at Loop Street Police Station and the vehicle taken to the pound. Case has been opened at Camperdown Police Station,” said Suleiman on Sunday.